<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-05-26T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-05-26T23:00:00-05:00" n="349" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d349">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/654: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-05-27T12:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">May 27,
                                        1927—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received May 27—6:05
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>593. Legation’s 580, May 23, 3 p.m.; and 588, May 25, 4 p.m. Lockhart
                            reports that, Standard Oil Company having approved, their vessels <hi rend="italic">Mei Foo</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Mei Chuen</hi> left
                            for Ichang morning 26th escorted by U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Pigeon</hi> to evacuate oil stocks.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>